essionTranscriptPath` from `WriteCommittedOptions` and `TranscriptPath` from `CommittedMetadata`\\n3. **Compute paths at restore time**: Changed `RestoreLogsOnly` and `classifySessionsForRestore` to compute transcript paths from current repo location instead of using stored metadata\\n\\nFiles changed:\\n- cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/gemini.go\\n- cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/gemini_test.go\\n- cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/checkpoint.go\\n- cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/committed.go\\n- cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/resume_relocated_repo_test.go (new)\\n- cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go\\n- cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go\\n- cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_rewind.go\\n\\nDo a critical code review focusing on:\\n1. Correctness of the fix\\n2. Backwards compatibility with existing checkpoints\\n3. Any edge cases or potential issues\\n4. Code quality and test coverage\\n5. Security considerations\\n\\nRead the relevant files to understand the changes in context, then provide a thorough review.\",\"agentId\":\"ae40930\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01BJz7oHLMbMpjj98zdRv8Ey\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01N4zSdBduPnhz6S1ivrFxiP\",\"uuid\":\"067f5c83-4ee6-4437-a549-bf2b3d2a4cf6\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-18T09:22:15.097Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"067f5c83-4ee6-4437-a549-bf2b3d2a4cf6\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"630e8fc3-9c8a-4518-aa87-9c1d6f1e40f5\",\"version\":\"2.1.17\",\"gitBranch\":\"gtrrz-victor/fix-restore-sessions\",\"slug\":\"declarative-waddling-rose\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-18T09:23:05.053Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-5-20251101\",\"id\":\"msg_01SDCTdVxxEcjSF3zZ9xckH3\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_0116PTyBB8YDC11q4p5yQufT\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/docs/requirements/fix-restore-sessions/review-01.md\",\"content\":\"# Review 01\\n\\n> Status: pending-dev\\n> Date: 2026-02-18\\n> Reviewer: Code Review Agent\\n> Verdict: REQUEST CHANGES\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nPR #403 fixes issue #402 where `entire resume` fails when a project is moved to a different location. The fix has two main components:\\n\\n1. **Gemini path hashing**: Changed from regex sanitization (`SanitizePathForGemini`) to SHA256 hashing (`GetProjectHash`) to match Gemini CLI's actual behavior\\n2. **Remove stored transcript paths**: Stopped persisting `SessionTranscriptPath` in checkpoint metadata, instead computing paths at restore time from the current repo location\\n\\nThe approach is fundamentally sound and addresses the root cause correctly. However, there are several issues that should be addressed before merging.\\n\\n## Critical (Must Fix)\\n\\n### 1. **[checkpoint/checkpoint.go:289-292]** Inconsistent removal of `SessionTranscriptPath`\\n\\nThe PR removes `SessionTranscriptPath` from `WriteCommittedOptions` but leaves `TranscriptPath` in `CommittedMetadata` without any deprecation comment or removal. According to the PR description, `TranscriptPath` was removed from `CommittedMetadata`, but the diff shows only the comment and field were removed from `WriteCommittedOptions`.\\n\\nLooking at the main branch vs PR branch:\\n- `WriteCommittedOptions.SessionTranscriptPath` - **REMOVED** (correct)\\n- `CommittedMetadata.TranscriptPath` - Still present in both branches (the JSON field `transcript_path`)\\n\\nThe PR description claims `TranscriptPath` was removed from `CommittedMetadata`, but examining `checkpoint/checkpoint.go` shows it's still there in both versions. The diff only shows removal from `WriteCommittedOptions`.\\n\\n**Impact**: The `CommittedMetadata.TranscriptPath` field is still present and being read at restore time, but never written. This is actually fine for backward compatibility, but the PR description is misleading. Please clarify:\\n- Is `CommittedMetadata.TranscriptPath` intentionally kept for reading old checkpoints?\\n- If so, add a `// DEPRECATED` comment explaining it's read-only for backward compat\\n\\n### 2. **[manual_commit_rewind.go:707-717]** `resolveTranscriptPathFromMetadata` removed but referenced in comments\\n\\nThe function `resolveTranscriptPathFromMetadata()` was removed, but there's still a reference to it in `ResolveSessionFilePath` docstring at line 777-780:\\n\\n```go\\n// ResolveSessionFilePath determines the correct file path for an agent's session transcript.\\n// Checks session state for transcript_path first (needed for agents like Gemini that store\\n// transcripts at paths that GetSessionDir can't reconstruct, e.g. SHA-256 hashed directories).\\n```\\n\\nThis comment is now misleading because:\\n1. The code now uses `GetProjectHash()` which CAN reconstruct SHA-256 hashed directories\\n2. The function still checks session state, but that's for active sessions, not checkpoint restore\\n\\n**Fix**: Update the docstring to reflect the new behavior.\\n\\n## Important (Should Fix)\\n\\n### 3. **[geminicli/gemini.go:182-184]** Fallback filename uses `time.Now()` which may cause issues\\n\\nThe new fallback behavior in `ResolveSessionFile`:\\n```go\\ntimestamp := time.Now().UTC().Format(\\\"2006-01-02T15-04\\\")\\nreturn filepath.Join(sessionDir, \\\"session-\\\"+timestamp+\\\"-\\\"+shortID+\\\".json\\\")\\n```\\n\\nThis creates a non-deterministic filename that changes every minute. For restore operations:\\n- If called twice within the same minute, it returns the same path (good)\\n- If called at minute boundary, you could get different paths (edge case)\\n\\nMore importantly, **Gemini CLI itself doesn't use this pattern for creating new files** - it only uses it for reading existing files. The fallback should either:\\n1. Only be used when there's NO existing file (current behavior, but filename won't match)\\n2. Match what Gemini CLI actually does when creating a new session\\n\\nThis is low risk for the restore use case since restore writes to this path, but inconsistent with Gemini's actual naming if Gemini later tries to find this file.\\n\\n### 4. **[e2e_test/resume_relocated_repo_test.go]** Test only covers Claude Code, not Gemini\\n\\nThe E2E test is well-structured but only validates Claude Code's `SanitizePathForClaude()`. Since a significant part of this PR is fixing Gemini's path hashing, consider adding a test that verifies Gemini session restore works with the new SHA256 hashing.\\n\\n### 5. **[common.go:238-254]** Removed `homeRelativePath` but it was a useful utility\\n\\nThe removal of `homeRelativePath()` is correct since it's no longer used, but if other code paths need home-relative paths in the future, this would need to be re-added. Consider whether this utility might be useful elsewhere.\\n\\n## Suggestions (Consider)\\n\\n### 6. Consider adding backward compatibility documentation\\n\\nThe change to compute paths at restore time has backward compatibility implications:\\n- Old checkpoints with stored `transcript_path` will now be ignored\\n- This is **intentional** and **correct** (the stored path is stale)\\n- But it might surprise users who expect the stored path to be used\\n\\nConsider adding a comment in `RestoreLogsOnly()` explaining why stored paths are ignored:\\n```go\\n// Compute transcript path from current repo location.\\n// Note: We intentionally ignore CommittedMetadata.TranscriptPath (if present)\\n// because that path is relative to where the checkpoint was created, which\\n// may differ from the current repo location after moves or cross-machine clones.\\n```\\n\\n### 7. **[geminicli/gemini_test.go:453-473]** Test improvements\\n\\nThe `TestGetProjectHash` test is good but could be more robust:\\n- Verify the hash matches what Gemini CLI produces (if known)\\n- Test edge cases: empty path, paths with special characters, Unicode paths\\n\\n## Praise\\n\\n- **Good architectural decision**: Computing